    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "16 January 1950",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "(THIS IS REHAS OSI 8 DTD 14 JAN 50. CATEGORY BAKER MESSAGE).",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "     Rudy Fick says flying saucers from Venus came to earth by accident.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "Fudy Fick, well known Kansas City auto dealer stopped in Denver 2 weeks",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "ago while returning from Ogden, Utah. At that time he called on the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "manager of Ford Agency. Their conversation was interrupted by some",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "engineers arriving for a meeting; one of whom was a man named",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "Coulter. Coulter revealed some startling information. He (Coulter)",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "stated he \"crashed the Gate\" at a radar station near New Mexico and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "Arizona borders, and while there he saw 2 of the highly secret",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "\"Flying Saucers.\" Spot report details--the information contained",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "herein was furnished from article which appeared in the Wyandotte",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "Echo newspaper, Kansas City, Kansas, 6 January 1950. Of the two",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "Flying Saucers one was badly damaged and the other almost perfectly",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "intact. They consisted of 2 parts, a cockpit or cabin about 6 feet",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "in diameter. A ring 13 feet across and 2 feet thick surrounded",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "the cabin. The cabin was constructed of metal resembling aluminum,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "but the actual make of the metal has defied analysis. Coulter had",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "a piece of the metal in his possession and gave it to the Ford man to",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "send to the Dearborn plant for analysis. This man (Coulter) showed",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "the group, including Fick, a clock or automatic calendar which was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "taken from one of the Flying Saucers. This clock or automatic",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "calendar consisted of 2 pieces of metal together with some unusual",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "type of metal. On the face of 1 or 2 pieces of this metal there",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "text": "appeared an indentation which rotated around the disk completing a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "cycle each 28 days. According to the information given Coulter",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "around 50 of these flying saucers have been found in the United",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 48,
      "text": "States in a period of 2 years. Of these, 40 are in the 7 US Research",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 49,
      "text": "Bureaus in Los Angeles. Each of the craft had a crew of 3. The bodies",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 50,
      "text": "in the damaged ship were charred, but the other ship's occupants were",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 51,
      "text": "in a perfect state of preservation, although dead.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 52,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
